Moultrie Patten https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moultrie_Patten 0 Moultrie Patten (June 10, 1919 – March 18, 2009) was an American actor and jazz musician. Patten was perhaps best known for his role as Walt the trapper on the American television series, Northern Exposure, which aired from 1990 until 1995. Patten appeared as Walt Kupfer from 1993 until the show's ending in 1995. Moultrie_Patten ( June_10_,_1919 – March_18_,_2009 ) was an_American_actor_and_jazz_musician .
